DECORATOR INTERVIEW ADDITIONS (IMPORTANT)
=================================================

1. DECORATOR VS ADAPTER
-------------------------------------------------

Decorator:
-----------
Purpose:
Add new functionality to an existing object.

Focus:
-------
Behavior Extension

Example:
--------
PlainPizza
    |
Cheese
    |
Olives

Result:
-------
New features added dynamically.

Memory Trick:
-------------
Decorator = Feature Adder

-------------------------------------------------

Adapter:
---------
Purpose:
Convert one interface into another interface
expected by the client.

Focus:
-------
Interface Conversion

Example:
--------
analysedata()
        ↓
getxmldata()

Result:
-------
Incompatible classes work together.

Memory Trick:
-------------
Adapter = Translator

-------------------------------------------------

INTERVIEW ONE-LINER:
--------------------
Decorator adds functionality.
Adapter converts interfaces.

=================================================
2. DECORATOR VS INHERITANCE
=================================================

Inheritance Approach:
---------------------

Pizza

├── PizzaWithCheese
├── PizzaWithOlives
├── PizzaWithMushroom
├── PizzaWithCheeseOlives
├── PizzaWithCheeseMushroom
├── PizzaWithOlivesMushroom
└── PizzaWithCheeseOlivesMushroom

Problems:
---------
❌ Too many subclasses
❌ Hard to maintain
❌ Not flexible at runtime

This is called:
---------------
CLASS EXPLOSION

-------------------------------------------------

Decorator Approach:
-------------------

PlainPizza
      |
Cheese Decorator
      |
Olives Decorator
      |
Mushroom Decorator

Benefits:
---------
✔ No class explosion
✔ Runtime flexibility
✔ Better code reuse
✔ Follows Open/Closed Principle

-------------------------------------------------

INTERVIEW ONE-LINER:
--------------------
Inheritance adds behavior at compile time,
while Decorator adds behavior dynamically
at runtime.

=================================================
3. WHY NOT USE INHERITANCE?
(COMMON INTERVIEW QUESTION)
=================================================

Question:
---------
Why do we need Decorator Pattern when
inheritance already exists?

Answer:
-------

Inheritance creates a new subclass for every
possible feature combination.

For example:

Pizza
PizzaWithCheese
PizzaWithOlives
PizzaWithCheeseAndOlives
PizzaWithCheeseAndOlivesAndMushroom

As features increase, the number of subclasses
grows rapidly, leading to class explosion.

Decorator Pattern solves this problem by
allowing features to be combined dynamically
at runtime through object composition.

Benefits:
---------
✔ No subclass explosion
✔ Runtime flexibility
✔ Better maintainability
✔ Reusable decorators
✔ Follows Open/Closed Principle

-------------------------------------------------

INTERVIEW ONE-LINER:
--------------------
Decorator is preferred over inheritance when
features need to be combined dynamically at
runtime without creating many subclasses.

